  <!-- SECTION 4: SETUP -->
  <div class="sec-mark" id="setup">04 &mdash; Complete 6-step setup guide</div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>How to Set Up Shopify Agentic Storefronts (Step-by-Step)</h2>
    <p>Total setup time: approximately 45 minutes if your product catalog is already well-organised. Allow 90 minutes if you need to clean product descriptions and add policies first.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="step-list">
    <div class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num-col"><span class="step-n">1</span></div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <div class="step-title">Check Eligibility <span class="step-req-tag sr-req">required first</span></div>
        <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Shopify Admin &rarr; Settings &rarr; Apps and sales channels</strong>. Look for an &ldquo;Agentic Storefronts&rdquo; section. If it&apos;s there, you&apos;re eligible. If not, the section will not appear &mdash; see Section 9 for what to do.</div>
        <span class="step-time">&#9203; 2 minutes</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num-col"><span class="step-n">2</span></div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <div class="step-title">Add Store Policies <span class="step-req-tag sr-req">required</span></div>
        <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Shopify Admin &rarr; Settings &rarr; Policies</strong>. Ensure you have a Terms of Service, Privacy Policy, and Refund Policy published. These must be live before you can activate Agentic Storefronts. Shopify&apos;s policy generator can create compliant templates if you don&apos;t have them.</div>
        <span class="step-time">&#9203; 5&ndash;10 minutes</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num-col"><span class="step-n">3</span></div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <div class="step-title">Install the Knowledge Base App <span class="step-req-tag sr-rec">strongly recommended</span></div>
        <div class="step-desc">Search <strong>&ldquo;Knowledge Base&rdquo;</strong> in the Shopify App Store, or navigate to <strong>Settings &rarr; Apps and channels &rarr; Knowledge Base App</strong>. Free for Shopify Plus. <strong>$50/month</strong> for standard plans. Activate it, then create your first knowledge base &mdash; include FAQs, return policies, shipping information, and brand voice guidelines. AI agents use this to give accurate, on-brand answers. See Section 5 for exactly what to write.</div>
        <span class="step-time">&#9203; 20&ndash;30 minutes</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num-col"><span class="step-n">4</span></div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <div class="step-title">Optimise Your Product Catalog <span class="step-req-tag sr-rec">strongly recommended</span></div>
        <div class="step-desc">Ensure every product has: a <strong>complete descriptive title</strong> (brand + product + key spec), a <strong>detailed description</strong> (200+ words covering materials, sizing, use cases), <strong>all variants defined</strong> with accurate stock, <strong>current pricing</strong>, and <strong>high-quality images</strong>. Add relevant metafields. Use Shopify&apos;s Catalog Mapping for custom product data structures. See Section 6 for the full product data checklist.</div>
        <span class="step-time">&#9203; Variable &mdash; depends on catalog size</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num-col"><span class="step-n">5</span></div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <div class="step-title">Enable Agentic Storefront Channels <span class="step-req-tag sr-new">activation</span></div>
        <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Settings &rarr; Apps and sales channels &rarr; Agentic Storefronts</strong>. Read and agree to the Supplemental Terms of Service. Toggle on each AI channel individually: <strong>ChatGPT</strong>, <strong>Google AI Mode and Gemini</strong>, and <strong>Microsoft Copilot</strong>. Each channel has a separate toggle. You can enable them individually or all at once.</div>
        <span class="step-time">&#9203; 5 minutes</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-item">
      <div class="step-num-col"><span class="step-n">6</span></div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <div class="step-title">Verify and Monitor <span class="step-req-tag sr-opt">ongoing</span></div>
        <div class="step-desc">Go to <strong>Agentic Storefronts &rarr; Test Agent</strong> to verify your products appear correctly in simulated AI queries. Monitor AI-attributed orders in your <strong>Orders list, filtered by channel</strong>. Review search trend data and FAQ insights in your Agentic Storefronts dashboard to understand what customers are asking AI agents about your products.</div>
        <span class="step-time">&#9203; Ongoing</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 5: KNOWLEDGE BASE -->
  <div class="sec-mark" id="knowledge-base">05 &mdash; Knowledge Base App</div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>The Knowledge Base App &mdash; What to Actually Write</h2>
    <p>The Knowledge Base App is the most under-used part of Agentic Storefronts. It&apos;s invisible to your customers but directly shapes what AI agents say about your products. When a customer asks &ldquo;does this store have a good return policy?&rdquo;, the AI answers from your Knowledge Base content &mdash; not by scraping your website.</p>
    <p>Most merchants activate it and write nothing useful. Here&apos;s what to actually include:</p>

    <h3>1. FAQs &mdash; Write for the Questions AI Agents Get Asked</h3>
    <p>Think about what customers ask during the purchase decision phase. Write at least 15&ndash;20 Q&amp;As covering: shipping times and costs, return and refund policy (specifics, not generalities), product sizing and fit guidance, materials and care instructions, warranty and quality guarantees, and your brand&apos;s core differentiators. Write answers in plain, direct language &mdash; AI agents paraphrase content, so clarity matters more than marketing tone.</p>

    <h3>2. Return and Refund Policy (Detailed Version)</h3>
    <p>Your Shopify policies page is a legal document. Your Knowledge Base entry should be the <em>customer-friendly</em> version: what the process actually involves, how long refunds take, what &ldquo;free returns&rdquo; means in practice, and any exceptions. AI agents will cite this when answering return questions &mdash; make it accurate and reassuring.</p>

    <h3>3. Brand Voice Guidelines</h3>
    <p>Tell the AI how to represent your brand. Specify: formal or casual tone, key phrases you want used or avoided, how to describe your core product benefits, and any regulatory or compliance language to include or exclude. This is particularly important for supplements, medical devices, or regulated products where AI paraphrasing could create compliance issues.</p>

    <h3>4. Shipping and Fulfilment Information</h3>
    <p>Processing times, carrier options, tracked vs untracked shipping, delivery estimates by region, international shipping availability, and what happens if an order is delayed. Be specific &mdash; &ldquo;3&ndash;5 business days&rdquo; is more useful than &ldquo;fast shipping&rdquo;.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="inline-cta green">
    <div class="ict-text">
      <h4>Replacing your tracking stack at the same time?</h4>
      <p>CAPI Shield gives you free server-side tracking for Meta &amp; Google &mdash; critical because Agentic Storefronts only fires server-side pixels.</p>
    </div>
    <a href="https://stackarchitect.xyz/capi-shield" class="btn btn-g">See CAPI Shield &rarr;</a>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 6: PRODUCT DATA -->
  <div class="sec-mark" id="product-data">06 &mdash; Product data optimisation for AI</div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Optimising Your Product Data for AI Discovery</h2>
    <p>AI agents are not search engines. They don&apos;t just match keywords &mdash; they interpret intent and match products to conversational queries. A product titled &ldquo;Blue Sneaker&rdquo; will lose to &ldquo;Men&apos;s Wide-Fit Running Sneaker &mdash; Breathable Mesh, Cushioned Sole, UK 7&ndash;13&rdquo; when a customer asks ChatGPT for a comfortable wide-fit running shoe.</p>

    <h3>Product Title Formula</h3>
    <p>Use: <strong>[Brand] + [Product Type] + [Key Differentiator] + [Size/Variant Info if relevant]</strong>. Aim for 60&ndash;80 characters. Include the words customers actually use in conversation, not internal product codes.</p>

    <h3>Product Description Requirements</h3>
    <p>Minimum 200 words. Cover: what the product is (plain language first sentence), key materials and specifications, who it&apos;s designed for and in what use case, how it compares to common alternatives, care and maintenance, and any certifications or quality guarantees. Use short paragraphs and bullet points &mdash; AI agents parse structured content more reliably than dense prose.</p>

    <h3>Variant and Inventory Accuracy</h3>
    <p>AI agents will not recommend products that show as out of stock. Keep inventory counts current. Define all variants explicitly &mdash; if you sell in 5 colours and 8 sizes, all 40 combinations should be defined with accurate stock counts. Vague &ldquo;multiple options available&rdquo; descriptions hurt AI recommendations.</p>

    <h3>Metafields for AI Context</h3>
    <p>Add metafields for: material composition, care instructions, age/gender suitability, country of manufacture, certifications, and compatible products. AI agents can use metafield data to answer specific questions your product description doesn&apos;t cover.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- SECTION 7: LIMITATIONS -->
  <div class="sec-mark" id="limitations">07 &mdash; Limitations</div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Agentic Storefronts Limitations (March 2026)</h2>
    <p>These are the limitations that matter most for your operations. Read this section before enabling &mdash; several have direct revenue and compliance implications.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table class="lim-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Limitation</th>
          <th>Impact level</th>
          <th>Workaround</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="col-lim">US-only availability</td>
          <td class="col-impact">HIGH &mdash; blocks non-US stores</td>
          <td class="col-fix">Use Section 9 prep steps; sign up for early access</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="col-lim">No GA4 or browser pixel tracking in agentic checkout</td>
          <td class="col-impact">HIGH &mdash; tracking gap</td>
